Description: Shoulder sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; white slip; exterior: series of painted tongues with line below.
Curator's comments: The sherd probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1886,0401.779a-h, but does not join; there is a slight possibility that part of a graffito stroke is preserved at the right edge.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.123)
